{"TopicId":39221,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Proposed orbiter emergency escape system","CreatedByName":"Runescope","CreatedById":2947,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-26T21:48:38Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Runescope","CreatedById":2947,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-26T21:48:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EGreetings! I\u0027m trying to find out what the proposed orbiter emergency escape system was called. I don\u0027t think it was ever used, and it was a single person capsule that was basically a coffin with a rocket and a parachute. Usually I can google something like this, but I seem to be having a bad day and the G-Man is letting me down. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf anyone knows, I\u0027d appreciate it!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"astropapi1","CreatedById":57507,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-26T21:50:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI think you\u0027re talking about \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MOOSE\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EMOOSE\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EScott Manley talked about it. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Runescope","CreatedById":2947,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-26T22:06:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:36px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:impact;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Ethat\u0027s the pickle!\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"astropapi1","CreatedById":57507,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-26T22:44:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Runescope\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Runescope\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:36px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:impact;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Ethat\u0027s the pickle!\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:8px;\u0022\u003EYay! \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E (10char)\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-27T01:50:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022astropapi1\u0022 data-cite=\u0022astropapi1\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EI think you\u0027re talking about \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MOOSE\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EMOOSE\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cp\u003EScott Manley talked about it. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMoose was not an coffin it was an ejection seat with an inflatable foam heat shield. Yes its far more kerbal than the orion nuclear rocket.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Seret","CreatedById":41409,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-28T14:52:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThere have been a few escape systems proposed over the years. There were some clamshell designs like those on the B-58, and IIRC one of the early designs for the shuttle used an escape capsule like the B-1 and F-117. Buran had ejection seats, as did the European Hermes design.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENone of them are useful through all stages of launch or re-entry, which is why they\u0027ve not been very popular.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}